20Trump%20and%20Fred%20Trump%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F675c7373ec3fba82bfa90d45%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221982%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EDonald%20Trump%20took%20over%20the%20business%20from%20his%20father%20in%201971%20and%20renamed%20it%20in%201973.%3Cp%3ESonia%20Moskowitz%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20president-elect%20was%20involved%20with%20the%20business%20since%20childhood%20and%20began%20officially%20working%20for%20his%20father%20shortly%20after%20graduating%20college.%20He%20took%20over%20the%20company%20in%201971%20and%20renamed%20it%20in%201973.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e34e08b8-a45a-4029-80b1-132bdc116e3e%5C%22%3EKey%20business%20areas%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Ch3%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22b69b4db8-242c-46cb-9f1d-2859dd00511e%5C%22%3EReal%20estate%3C%2Fh3%3E%3Cp%3EAfter%20taking%20over%2C%20Trump%20helped%20expand%20the%20business%2C%20buying%20properties%20in%20Manhattan%20and%20outside%20of%20New%20York.%20He%20developed%20the%20Grand%20Hyatt%20Hotel%20in%201976%2C%20despite%20not%20having%20enough%20money%20to%20buy%20the%20property%20(this%20is%20among%20the%20early%20plot%20points%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fthe-apprentice-donald-trump-biopic-fact-fiction-movie-2024-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E'The%20Apprentice%2C%3C%2Fa%3E'%20a%202024%20movie%20about%20Trump's%20business%20rise).%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%201980s%2C%20Trump%20had%20established%20himself%20as%20a%20real%20estate%20mogul%2C%20boasting%20properties%20like%20Trump%20Tower%20and%20beginning%20to%20pursue%20casinos%20in%20Atlantic%20City%2C%20New%20Jersey.%20The%20Trump%20Organization%20faced%20financial%20challenges%20in%20these%20years%2C%20with%20multiple%20Trump-owned%20properties%20filing%20for%20bankruptcy%20in%20the%20early%201990s.%20The%20president-elect%20used%20bankruptcy%20protections%20to%20restructure%20the%20company's%20debts%