20can%20be%20solved%20through%20fiat%26quot%3B%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Switzerland%20Revokes%20India's%20Most-Friendly-Nation%20Status%20Over%20Nestle%20Verdict%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3ESwitzerland%20has%20taken%20a%20unilateral%20stand%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India's%20ruling%20in%20the%20Nestle%20case.%20It%20has%20revoked%20the%20'Most%20Friendly%20Nation'%20or%20MFN%20status%20accorded%20to%20India%20under%20the%20Double%20Taxation%20Avoidance%20Agreement%20or%20DTAA%20treaty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwitzerland's%20move%20marks%20a%20significant%20shift%20in%20bilateral%20treaty%20dynamics%20and%20will%20result%20in%20a%20big%20impact%20on%20Indian%20companies%20operating%20in%20Switzerland%20as%20well%20as%20on%20Swiss%20investments%20in%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20its%20official%20statement%20on%20December%2011%2C%20the%20Swiss%20finance%20department%20named%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India%20and%20cited%20its%202023%20ruling%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20its%20decision%20to%20remove%20India's%20MFN%20status.%20In%20its%20order%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20had%20said%20that%20the%20MFN%20clause%20between%20two%20nations%20does%20not%20apply%20automatically%20when%20a%20country%20joins%20the%20OECD%2C%20especially%20if%20the%20Indian%20government%20already%20had%20a%20prior%20tax%20treaty%20with%20that%20country%20before%20joining%20the%20grouping.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20OECD%20or%20Organisation%20for%20Economic%20Co-operation%20and%20Development%20was%20established%20in%201961%20and%20is%20headquartered%20in%20Paris.%20It%20calls%20itself%20a%20forum%20and%20knowledge%20hub%20for%20data%2C%20analysis%2C%20and%20best%20practices%20in%20public%20policy%20to%20build%20stronger%2C%20fairer%2C%20and%20cleaner%20societies%20-%20helping%20to%20shape%20better%20policies%20for%20better%20lives.%20It%20works%20closely%20with%20policy%20makers%2C%20stakeholders%20and%20citizens%20to%20establish%20evidence-based%20international%20standards%20and%20to%20find%20solutions%20to%20social%2C%20economic%20and%20environmental%20challenges.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EA%20HISTORY%20TO%20THE%20CASE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIndia%20had%20signed%20tax%20agreements%20with%20Lithuania%20and%20Colombia%20under%20which%20the%20tax%20rates%20on%20certain%20types%20of%20income%20were%20lower%20than%20the%20rates%20it%20provided%20to%20OECD%20countries.%20Both%20countries%20later%20joined%20the%20OECD.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EUnder%20the%20OECD%2C%20the%20effect%20of%20an%20MFN%20clause%20is%20that%20one%20country%20obligates%20itself%20to%20its%20treaty%20partner%20with%20respect%20to%20offering%20it%20a%20'more%20favourable'%20tax%20treatment.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwitzerland%20assumed%20that%20Colombia%20and%20Lithuania%20joining%20the%20OECD%20meant%20a%205%20per%20cent%20rate%20for%20dividends%20would%20apply%20to%20the%20India-Switzerland%20tax%20treaty%20under%20the%20MFN%20clause%2C%20instead%20of%20the%2010%20per%20cent%20which%20was%20mentioned%20in%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBut%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20meant%20otherwise%20--%20that%20the%20MFN%20clause%20between%20two%20nations%20does%20not%20apply%20automatically%20when%20a%20country%20joins%20the%20OECD%2C%20and%20that%20the%20prior%20tax%20treaty%20takes%20precedence%2C%20unless%20the%20MFN%20clause%20is%20specifically%20mentioned%20in%20a%20'notification'%20in%20accordance%20with%20Section%2090%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20THIS%20MEANT%20FOR%20THE%20NESTLE%20CASE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20statement%20by%20Switzerland's%20finance%20department%2C%20in%202021%2C%20the%20Delhi%20High%20Court%20while%20hearing%20the%20case%20against%20Nestle%2C%20upheld%20the%20applicability%20of%20the%20residual%20tax%20rates%20after%20taking%20into%20account%20the%20MFN%20clause%20under%20the%20Double%20Taxation%20Avoidance%20Agreement.%20This%20was%20in%20line%20with%20how%20Switzerland%20had%20interpreted%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20in%20a%20ruling%20dated%20October%2019%2C%202023%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20reversed%20the%20high%20court's%20judgement%20and%20stated%20that%2C%20the%20applicability%20of%20the%20MFN%20clause%20was%20not%20triggered%20automatically.%20The%20top%20court%20ruled%20that%20the%20MFN%20clause%20%26quot%3Bwas%20not%20directly%20applicable%20in%20the%20absence%20of%20'notification'%20in%20accordance%20with%20Section%2090%20of%20the%20Income%20Tax%20Act%26quot%3B%20-%20a%20ruling%20that%20impacted%20Nestle%20and%20in-turn%20went%20against%20what%20Switzerland%20had%20hoped%20for.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3ESWITZERLAND'S%20RESPONSE%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESwitzerland%20has%20now%20responded%20by%20unilaterally%20revoking%20India's%20MFN%20status%20and%20squarely%20named%20the%20%26quot%3BIndian%20Supreme%20Court%26quot%3B%20as%20the%20reason%20for%20its%20decision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20means%20that%20from%20January%201%2C%202025%2C%20Switzerland%20will%20levy%20a%2010%20per%20cent%20tax%20(instead%20of%20the%20current%205%20per%20cent)%20on%20dividends%20payable%20to%20Indian%20tax%20residents%20and%20entities%20who%20claim%20refunds%20for%20Swiss%20withholding%20tax%20and%20for%20Swiss%20tax%20residents%20who%20claim%20foreign%20tax%20credits.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20Swiss%20Finance%20Department%20released%20a%20statement%20in%20which%20it%20announced%20%26quot%3BSuspension%20of%20the%20application%20of%20the%20MFN%20clause%20of%20the%20protocol%20to%20the%20agreement%20between%20the%20Swiss%20Confederation%20and%20the%20Republic%20of%20India%20for%20the%20avoidance%20of%20double%20taxation%20with%20respect%20to%20taxes%20on%20income.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20statement%20cited%20the%20%26quot%3B2023%20ruling%20by%20Indian%20Supreme%20Court%26quot%3B%20in%20a%20case%20relating%20to%20Nestle%20for%20its%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20the%20MFN%20status.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3EWHAT%20EXPERTS%20SAY%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESome%20see%20Switzerland's%20move%20as%20a%20retaliatory%20measure%20to%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%2C%20while%20others%20see%20this%20as%20a%20measure%20of%20reciprocity.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENangia%20Andersen%20M%26amp%3BA%20Tax%20Partner%20Sandeep%20Jhunjhunwala%20called%20Switzerland's%20move%20unilateral%20and%20said%20%26quot%3BThis%20suspension%20may%20lead%20to%20increased%20tax%20liabilities%20for%20Indian%20entities%20operating%20in%20Switzerland%2C%20highlighting%20the%20complexities%20of%20navigating%20international%20tax%20treaties%20in%20an%20evolving%20global%20landscape.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt%20also%20underscores%20the%20necessity%20of%20aligning%20treaty%20partners%20on%20the%20interpretation%20and%20application%20of%20tax%20treaty%20clauses%20to%20ensure%20predictability%2C%20equity%2C%20and%20stability%20in%20international%20tax%20framework%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Jhunjhunwala%20told%20news%20agency%20Press%20Trust%20of%20India.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAKM%20Global%20Tax%20Partner%2C%20Amit%20Maheshwari%2C%20said%20that%20%26quot%3BThe%20main%20reason%20behind%20the%20decision%20to%20withdraw%20MFN%20is%20of%20reciprocity%2C%20which%20ensures%20that%20taxpayers%20in%20both%20countries%20are%20treated%20equally%20and%20fairly.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BSwiss%20authorities%20announced%20in%20August%202021%20that%20based%20on%20the%20MFN%20clause%20between%20Switzerland%20and%20India%2C%20the%20tax%20rate%20on%20dividends%20from%20qualifying%20shareholdings%20would%20be%20reduced%20from%2010%20per%20cent%20to%205%20per%20cent%2C%20effective%20retroactively%20from%20July%205%2C%202018.%20However%2C%20the%20subsequent%20Supreme%20Court%20ruling%20in%202023%20contradicted%20the%20same%2C%26quot%3B%20Mr%20Maheshwari%20told%20PTI.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%20that%20%26quot%3BThis%20could%20impact%20Swiss%20investments%20in%20India%20as%20dividends%20would%20be%20subject%20to%20higher%20withholding%20now%20and%20income%20accruing%20on%20or%20after%20January%201%2C%202025%2C%20may%20be%20taxed%20at%20the%20rates%20provided%20for%20in%20the%20original%20double%20taxation%20treaty%20between%20Switzerland%20and%20India%2C%20regardless%20of%20the%20MFN%20clause.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EJSA%20Advocates%20%26amp%3B%20Solicitors%20Partner%20Kumarmanglam%20Vijay%20said%20%26quot%3BThis%20would%20especially%20impact%20Indian%20companies%20having%20ODI%20(overseas%20direct%20investment)%20structures%20with%20subsidiaries%20in%20Switzerland%20and%20will%20raise%20the%20Swiss%20withholding%20tax%20on%20dividends%20from%205%20per%20cent%20to%2010%20per%20cent%20from%20January%201%2C%202025.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3E(Inputs%20from%20PTI)%3C%2Fem%3E%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1734110520000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.ndtvimg.com%2Fi%2F2015-06%2Fnestle-logo_650x400_41433357775.jpg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fswitzerland-revokes-indias-most-friendly-nation-status-over-supreme-court-ruling-in-nestle-case-7242871%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Switzerland%20has%20taken%20a%20unilateral%20stand%20after%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20of%20India's%20ruling%20in%20the%20Nestle%20case.%20It%20has%20revoked%20the%20'Most%20Friendly%20Nation'%20or%20MFN%20status%20accorded%20to%20India%20under%20the%20Double%20Taxation%20Avoidance%20Agreement%20or%20DTAA%20treaty.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fswitzerland-revokes-indias-most-friendly-nation-status-over-supreme-court-ruling-in-nestle-case-7242871%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Allu's%20arrest%3A%20Telangana%20police%20reacts%20to%20viral%20letter%22%2