5C%22314%5C%22%3E%3C%2Fiframe%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3ESinghara%2C%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20the%20samosa%20is%20referred%20to%2C%20is%20one%20among%20many%20gems%20at%20this%20eatery.%20The%20others%20include%20cutlets%2C%20%3Cem%3Etelebhaja%20%3C%2Fem%3E(fritters)%2C%20and%20%3Cem%3Emughlai%20porota%3C%2Fem%3E%20(a%20flaky%20pan-fried%20%3Cem%3Eparatha%20%3C%2Fem%3Estuffed%20with%20meats).%20And%20accompanying%20every%20serving%20is%20ketchup%2C%20spicy%20green%20%3Cem%3Echutney%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20curd-based%20dip%2C%20and%20mustard%20sauce.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E3.%20Munni%20Lal%20Halwai%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWhen%20Professor%20Pushpesh%20Pant%2C%20one%20of%20the%20world%E2%80%99s%20experts%20on%20Indian%20food%2C%20described%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%20%3C%2Fem%3Eas%20a%20%E2%80%9Ccrude%20peasant%20dish%E2%80%9D%20once%20%E2%80%94%20he%20was%20referring%20to%20its%20ability%20to%20appease%20society%20at%20large.%20The%20moniker%20is%20attributed%20to%20the%20%3Cem%3Esamosa%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%99s%20no-frills%20recipe.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20instance%2C%20Munni%20Lal%20Halwai%20has%20been%20packing%20a%20punch%20in%20their%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%3C%2Fem%3E%20since%20the%201940s%20at%20a%20rate%20that%20won%E2%80%99t%20burn%20a%20hole%20in%20your%20pocket.%20And%20adding%20flavour%20to%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noreferrer%20noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthebetterindia.com%2F295271%2Forigin-of-chole-bhature-in-india-partition-food-history%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%20the%20classic%20is%20%3Cem%3Echole%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20(chickpea%20curry)%2C%20onions%20and%20%3Cem%3Epudhina%20%3C%2Fem%3E(mint)%3Cem%3E%20chutney%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Ch2%20class%3D%5C%22wp-block-heading%5C%22%3E4.%20Shri%20Bankey%20Bihari%20Samose%20Wale%3C%2Fh2%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20Paharganj%2C%20there%20lies%20a%20shop%20that%20has%20been%20doling%20out%20delicious%20%3Cem%3Esamosas%20%3C%2Fem%3Efor%20over%2060%20years%20now.%20The%20%3Cem